snippet.textDisplay: I'm from Rajasthan, India, on the other side of Thar. When she sang "The people of Thar were awakened," I got goosebumps. We're all the people of Thar, on both sides of the border, representing Rajasthan, India, and Sindh, Pakistan! The Thar Desert unites us. The culture, traditions, and clothing are exactly the same as what we have in rural Rajasthan, especially in Marwar! I'm so amazed and grateful to Coke Studio Pakistan and especially Xulfi for celebrating my culture ❤ Though I don't understand Sindhi, it's very similar to my Rajasthani Marwari language, but the culture of Thar is the same on both sides ❤️
snippet.textOriginal: I'm from Rajasthan, India, on the other side of Thar. When she sang "The people of Thar were awakened," I got goosebumps. We're all the people of Thar, on both sides of the border, representing Rajasthan, India, and Sindh, Pakistan! The Thar Desert unites us. The culture, traditions, and clothing are exactly the same as what we have in rural Rajasthan, especially in Marwar!
